await request(method, url, **kwargs)[source]#

The request function is a wrapper around the ClientSession.request function, which handles ratelimits and other exceptions that may occur during requests. It also adds an additional cooldown to the Retry-After header value.

Parameters:

  • method (str) – Determine the type of request

  • url (str) – Specify the url that you want to make a request to

  • kwargs (Any) – Pass in additional parameters to the request function

Return type:

ClientResponse

class asynccore.http.HTTPClient(api_version, loop, logger, request_latency, ratelimit_additional_cooldown, client, activity, startup_cache)[source]#

Bases: object

HTTPClient handles all requests related to the client. It also has methods from checking tokens or creating a new session.

Parameters:

  • api_version (Literal[9, 10]) – version of the discord api used by the client

  • loop (Optional[AbstractEventLoop]) – Set the event loop that will be used by the client

  • logger (bool) – Enable/disable the logger

  • request_latency (float) – Control the rate of requests sent to discord

  • ratelimit_additional_cooldown (float) – Add a cooldown to the ratelimit

  • client (Client) – Client object needed to connect to gateway

  • activity (Optional[ActivityBuilder]) – The argument with type AcivityBuilder is responsible for account activity.

  • startup_cache (bool) – Enable or disable cache fetching at program startup

await create_session()[source]#

The create_session function is used to create a new session for the Client. The session object contains all of the information that we need in order to connect with Discord’s API.

Return type:

None

await request(url, method, headers=None, data=None)[source]#

The request function is used to send a request to the API.

Parameters:

  • url (str) – Specify the url of the request

  • method (Literal['GET', 'POST', 'DELETE', 'PATCH', 'PUT']) – Specify the type of request being sent

  • headers (Optional[dict]) – Pass in a dictionary of headers to be sent with the request

  • data (Optional[dict]) – Send data to the api

Return type:

ClientResponse

run_async(function)[source]#

The run_async function is a helper function that allows you to run an asyncio coroutine in the background. It takes a single argument, which must be an awaitable object (such as a coroutine) It runs the event loop until the awaitable completes. This is useful for running tasks in parallel with other code.

Parameters:

function (Awaitable) – Specify the coroutine

Return type:

None
